    <p>RENEE MONTAGNE, HOST: </p>
    <p>The mandolin player Chris Thile is one of the most exciting talents in acoustic music. He made his name in bluegrass as a child star, but also plays classical and other genres, and he fronts a band that brings it all together. NPR's Vince Pearson reports on the latest from Punch Brothers.</p>
    <p>(SOUNDBITE OF SONG, "BETWEEN FIRST AND A")</p>
